Pain Threshold: You feel something -- like a swarm of hornets buzzing under your scalp. A strange tingling you can almost *smell*.
There it is again -- like a swarm of hornets buzzing under your scalp. A strange tingling you can almost *smell*.
You: "Do you think whatever happens will affect our cryptozoologists?"
Variable["coast.morell_greeting_done"]
Kim Kitsuragi: "Well... we're not responsible for what we can't predict, are we? I don't think the *entire* city will be razed to the ground." He smiles in the dark.
Esprit de Corps: Let's *try* not to worry, he thinks.
Logic: If you can't predict it, there's nothing you could have done.
Authority: He trusts your gut feeling on this.
You: "I saw them too. Footprints with the right sole worn smooth."
You: "You think it's the suspect who left the prints?"
You: "I saw them too, in the sand back there. Do you think it's our suspect?"
Kim Kitsuragi: He lowers his voice. "Once we detain a credible suspect, who knows what the Union and the Wild Pines will do? We'll set in motion events we have no control over."
Logic: You will upset the balance of power in Martinaise. The deadlock between the company and the Union will destabilize.
Savoir Faire: Not closely enough, you suspect. But still -- good idea to visit her once more.
Jump to: [mainhub]
Kim Kitsuragi: "Hmm..." He looks ahead, beyond the arch. "Either way, we ought to be careful. There were footprints back there. And I'm pretty sure they were fresh."
Untitled hub (02)
Kim Kitsuragi: "Looks like our suspect -- if she's in here, we need to plan our next step carefully."
You: "We know Evrart's true intentions *and* his plan for Martinaise. What more is there to do with the Union?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "I don't know, little things?" He pauses. "But you're right. We've gotten everything we can from the Union."
"I don't know, little things?" He pauses. "But you're right. We've gotten everything we can from the Union -- we even opened that container..."
"I don't know, little things?" He pauses. "But you're right. We've gotten everything we can from the Union -- we even did the borscht thing..."
Interfacing: You've been very, very thorough there. Your fingers approve.
Kim Kitsuragi: "You mean Lena? I don't see how cryptozoology and the murder investigation are connected. But... the situation in the city will get tense for everyone."
Reaction Speed: If it gets that tense, the amateur zoologists might not be able to do their job.
Untitled hub
You: "Nothing. It's just my mind playing tricks."
You: "A pain, a strange tingling."
You: "A ghost."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Possibly. If she's in here, we need to plan our next step carefully."
You: "We still don't know the full extent of Evrart's plans. I told Joyce -- maybe we should see Evrart again?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "I'll leave that to your judgement. You already know what I think about cross-pollinating information like this. It's dangerous, but..."
mainhub
You: [Discard thought.]
Pain Threshold: You can't, the sensation won't go away. It only gets worse...
You: "Hold on, you really don't feel anything?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "No -- but you're the sensitive one."
You: "We've met Joyce, but we don't know what she knows yet. We should probably find out."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Definitely. I think she knows something -- about the mercenaries, maybe. And she won't be around if the situation explodes."
Kim Kitsuragi: "No. What do you mean?"
You: "What do you mean?"
Rhetoric: It's not a quib. The situation is dangerous.
You: "We haven't met the Union leader yet. We should maybe get into the harbour before this?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "You're right, there won't be time to do that when the dominoes are falling. At the first sign of danger, they will shut the place down for good."
Esprit de Corps: ...in this case, we can't afford to be squeaky clean.
Kim Kitsuragi: "If you want to do that, then yes. We'd be advised to finish every lead. I don't think we'll have the chance to after..." He looks down the dark tunnel. He does not finish the thought.
You: "We've met the Union leader, but haven't gotten any info from him. Maybe we should talk to him more first?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "You're right, however corrupt he may be, nothing happens in Martinaise without him knowing. We might have to dirty our hands, but..."
Visual Calculus: He's right. That place is like a fortress. It's already almost impenetrable.
Kim Kitsuragi: "I don't feel it, but..." He looks ahead, beyond the arch. "We should still be careful. There were footprints back there. And I'm pretty sure they were fresh."
Interfacing: His hand rests on his holster. It's not enough -- you need a gun in your hand, too. *Your* gun.
You: "We know what Joyce knows about the murder -- but I may have *other things* to discuss with her."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Ah, yes. There won't be time for that once things go down. Matter of fact -- I don't think there's time for it *now*, but..."
Savoir Faire: I wouldn't be so sure. You haven't exactly been sneaking.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Or... maybe not." He puts his hand to his holster. "Either way, once we go deeper, there will be no turning back."
You: "Lieutenant, do you feel something?"
You: "I suddenly remembered -- we were running the serial number on the victim's armour..."
Kim Kitsuragi: "You think we should finish running it *now*?" he whispers. "Maybe you're right. It might not be as useful later..."
You: "How bad do you think things could get?"
Logic: It's a minor point. Don't worry too much about this. There are bigger fish.
You: "We haven't even met the company rep yet. We should find them first, no?"
You: "We've found out Evrart's plan to take the harbour -- maybe we should tell Joyce about it?"
You: "We solved the strike deadlock by telling Joyce about the Union's plans."
You: "We've still got a date with The Pigs... and *my gun*."
You: "Maybe we should finish looking into the Speedfreaks FM mystery?"
You: "Evrart knows more than he's told us. Maybe we should continue working for him?"
You: "What do you think is waiting for us there?" (Conclude.)
You: "We've checked the buoy with Klaasje's documents. I want to hear her take on why it was empty before."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Definitely. It amazes me how we've managed not to... The Wild Pines has information that may be critical to our case."
Esprit de Corps: ...if you must.
Volition: Keep calm. Go over the whole situation in detail.
Kim Kitsuragi: "We absolutely cannot skip that appointment." His face is stone. "Consider that 100% confirmed. I fear you'll need your gun for this..."
Kim Kitsuragi: "I still don't think that was a good idea, but, yes -- our affairs with the Wild Pines are in order. Since she isn't in Martinaise anymore."
Volition: Someone's been a very busy boy. Good on you...

Interfacing: This part of town is a fine clockwork puzzle. Disturb its peace and it will start breaking down -- uncontrollably.
Rhetoric: He just can't be sure -- maybe it will yield something useful?
Kim Kitsuragi: "I think I see a cavern..." The lieutenant's whisper echoes down the tunnel. "Maybe more cellars? I think we've been careful enough -- we still have the element of surprise."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Okay -- why not. Whatever goes down might also affect her. The Union is watching her closely now..."
